jsondiscoverer

Class JsonSimpleDiscoverer

  • java.lang.Object
    • jsondiscoverer.JsonSimpleDiscoverer

  • public class JsonSimpleDiscoverer
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is used to discover/refine metamodels (as EPackage elements) from JSON documents (i.e., json file).

    Once created, a metamodel out of a JsonSource element can be discovered by calling the method discover(JsonSource).

    To refine a metamodel, you have to call to refine(EPackage, JsonSource) giving the metamodel to refine and a new JsonSource.

    This implementation does not depend on Xtext (since v0.1.0)

    Author:
    Javier Canovas (me@jlcanovas.es)

    • Method Detail

      • discover

        public org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EPackage discover(JsonSource source)
        Launches the metamodel discoverer from a JSON document.

        The method receives a JsonSource element, which includes the set of JSON documents to be considered.

        The discovered metamodel is returned and also stored in the JsonSource received as param (calling AbstractJsonSource.setMetamodel(EPackage)).

        Parameters:
        source - The JsonSource including the JSON documents
        Returns:
        The metamodel (as EPackage)
